      'patcher-camp.subtitle': 'The Big Adventure Game',
      'patcher-camp.desc': 'Patcher Camp is a cooperative adventure game set across four climate zones, where young people solve real environmental problems using their skills as superpowers. The four elements (Earth, Water, Fire, Wind) represent different sustainability themes: materials, resources, energy, and mobility. Players work together to restore balance, complete real-life micro-tasks (cleaning, repair, cooking, upcycling), and unlock new abilities. There\u2019s also a Wizard Tent \u2014 a calm, reflective space with zero-waste recipes and debrief activities, designed especially for older teens (14\u201318).',
      'patcher-camp.why': 'Games make learning irresistible. Patcher Camp connects play to real-world action, helping young people see their skills as superpowers for the planet.',
      'patcher-camp.loopy': 'Loopy put on his adventure bandana and stepped into Patcher Camp. The forest around him shimmered. "Choose your element," the old tree spirit said. "Earth," Loopy said. "I want to help with materials." His badge glowed green. His first quest: find three things in the forest that could be reused instead of thrown away. He found an old jar (lantern!), a broken branch (walking stick!), and a torn net (plant holder!). "Three out of three," the tree spirit smiled. "You\u2019ve levelled up, Earth Patcher." Loopy grinned. He wasn\u2019t just playing a game. He was becoming someone who could fix the world, one small thing at a time.',

